node.text:
Following 48 Kenyan inmates contraction of coronavirus, the government has shutdown Kericho County correctional center to avoid further spread in the country.

The decision was reached after results of COVID-19 tests conducted inmates at GK correctional center provided a surge in community transmission of the novel virus among Kenyans.

Confirming decision to seal the premises, county governor, Paul Chepkwony, through a statement made available to newsmen yesterday, stated that the decision to embark on testing in correctional centers had yielded desired result.

The Kericho County administration was said to have made several decisions to mitigate spread of the virus, part of which was suspension of visits to inmates indefinitely.

Kenya remains the second worst hit country in Eastern African behind Ethiopia with 31,763 confirmed cases, which has also prompted court services in the county to be suspended for 14 days after four law officers tested positive to the virus.

shortcode_media.accessibility_caption: Photo by Community on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: 3 people, text that says '2020 COLLOQUIUM MARKS START OF NORTHWESTERN QATAR'S ACADEMIC YEAR L 1O GULF TIMES COMMUNITY'.

node.text:
Academic publishing during a pandemic and a preview of dean Marwan M Kraidy’s strategic priorities for Northwestern Qatar were main topics that were covered in this year's colloquium, an annual event for faculty and staff. The event also highlighted the research and creative output of the university’s faculty.
Dean Kraidy outlined his four strategic priorities for this year. The first of these, he said, is to “reposition the institution as a scholarly community that is involved in the production of original knowledge and storytelling of all kinds.”

Due to the global move to online learning, a transition Kraidy believes is accelerated but not ignited by Covid-19, Northwestern Qatar is able to continue distinguishing itself in this online environment by “focusing on what we do best, taking advantage of our location, and becoming more visible as a node for creating new knowledge and new stories.”

The importance of shared governance was the subject of Kraidy’s second strategic priority, which he defined as a “self-governing faculty that abide by a set of academic values and professional norms that are then translated into processes and procedures that are both clearly spelled out and equitable.” His third priority, relates to “faculty hiring, nurturing, promotion, and retention,” which he said is “a fundamental aspect of everything that we do and has to correspond to our mission.” The fourth and final priority addressed “a programme and agenda of research where everybody becomes known for a few fundamental questions and a variety of studies around them.”
.
.
.
.

Good afternoon everyone. I hope that you all are enjoying your weekend. It’s Saturday which means that Harper’s Classroom is here to provide information on how schools are planning to practice social distancing. Here in Texas, at GPISD the district has started the school year virtually. Teachers will give online instruction, while students remain in their homes. However, students are to return back to school September 8th, 2020, but parents are given the options of either allowing their student to receive instruction full-time in person, full-time online, or part-time i person with part-time online. 

Students and teachers are required to wear masks
Students and teachers are required to social distance from another by staying 6ft/2M apart.

【5 Seconds of Perth Today / 今日のパースの5秒】
.
5 Seconds of Perth Today on 22nd Aug 2020 is AFL Games at Optus Stadium.
.
Under Phase 4 in Western Australia AFL game took place at Optus Stadium on Saturday night. Fremantle Dockers won over the Sydney Swans at round 13. Stage 4 of roadmap allows sport and entertainment venues are still able to operate at a 50 per cent capacity rule　and 30,000 fans can attend AFL games at Optus Stadium.
.

.

node.text:
क्या कबीर! इतने उदास क्यों दिख रहे हो.
यार काव्या! धोनी ने रिटायरमेंट ले लिया. एक तो ये पेंडेमिक और अब ये न्यूज़; 
‘ये दुःख साला खत्म क्यों नहीं होता.’
हाँ! लेकिन, आज नहीं तो कल उसे रिटायरमेंट तो लेना ही था.
हाँ, सो तो है. लेकिन कम से कम एक लास्ट मैच तो और खेल लेना था. एक लास्ट बार हेलीकाप्टर शॉट लगाते देख लेते सब तो क्या हो जाता.
लेकिन कहते तो तब भी तुम यह ही कि उसे एक मैच और खेल लेना था. 
हाँ, शायद. लेकिन देखो तो ऐसे कोई लिखता है क्या- ‘पल दो पल मेरी हस्ती है, पल दो पल मेरी कहानी है’
धोनी की कहानी पल दो पल की है?
हाहाहा. कबीर! तुम बिलकुल इडियट हो. ऐसा है तो तुम कोई गाना डेडीकेट(Dedicate) कर दो अपनी ‘माही भाई’ को?
मेरे दिमाग में तो बस एक ही गाना चल रहा है – ‘कुछ लोग जो यूँ ही बिछड़ जाते हैं, वो हजारों के आने से मिलते नहीं.’
हाहाहा! कबीर, तुम पागल हो गए हो. अच्छा तुमको नहीं लगता वानखेड़े में धोनी का वो सिक्स और रवि शास्त्री की कॉमेंट्री एकदम परफेक्ट पोएट्री इन मोशन है. 
Wow. ऐसे तो कभी सोचा ही नहीं. You are a geneious.
Yes! I am.
क्या अब भी उदास हो.
हाँ!
अच्छा लॉकडाउन खत्म होने दो. तुमको कॉलेज के बाहर वाले सरदार जी के राजमा चावल खिलाऊँगी. जिंदगी के सारे दुःख भूल जाओगे! धोनी का रिटायरमेंट भी!
.
.
.

[Link in Bio] 🇱🇷 After five months, closed schools in the Liberian Republic have reopened. This is based on advice from Liberian health authorities, headed by Minister of Health Dr Wilhelmina Jallah.

🎓The senior students began schooling at the end of July, ended their preparations for the West African Senior Secondary Certification Examination (WASSCE), a type of standardized test which approves students graduation from secondary education.

📝❌With the presence of the merciless Covid-19, many Liberians are of the thinking that this year’s result of WASSCE will result in mass failure on grounds that schooling did not take place as is the norm pre-COVID-19.

The loss of the school year worries parents, students, and school principals. “We just hope that our children will try their best in the test because they did not have a longer time in the classrooms during this school year”, said James Kekulah, a father of two schooling children.

Pilli, pozitif vakalardan 8 kişinin  hava yolu, 1 kişinin deniz yoluyla ülkemize geldiğini, 2 vakanın daha önce tespit edilen pozitif vakanın temaslısı olduğunu ve bu süreçte gözetim altında olduğunu,  diğer 5 vakanın ise yeni havalimanı şantiyesinde çalışan işçiler arasından olduğunu belirtti. Pilli , Sağlık Bakanlığı ekipleri tarafından temaslı takibinin yapıldığını söyledi.

"Bugün Yapılan Test Sayısı 2070. Bugün saptanan Pozitif Vaka Sayısı 16. İyileşip Bugün Taburcu Edilen Vaka Sayısı 7. Bugün Kaybedilen Vaka yok. Yapılan Toplam Test Sayısı 107.011. Another way we are keeping things safe in the office! This air purifier is reported to achieve a 99.9999%, six log reduction, kill rate in a single air pass. The kill rate is used to describe what percentage of a given germ is killed by a particular process or disinfectant.

According to reports, when dealing with viruses, single air pass kill rates are critical to minimize the risk of cross contamination. Two key factors to consider when using technology to reduce airborne and droplet virus exposure are controlling the airflow to take the danger away from the breathing zone and purifying the air as it passes through the unit in a single air pass. While no technology is perfect we are using everything available to ensure patient safety. #covid #optometrist  #yorkville #pandemic #eyedoctor #safety #toronto #healthylifestyle #technology

node.text:
Kathleen Kennedy, la presidenta de Lucasfilm, ha concedido una entrevista para “The Wrap”, donde ha confirmado que lograron terminar el rodaje de la 2ª temporada de “The Mandalorian”, del universo de Star Wars, solo cinco días antes de que empezase el confinamiento por la pandemia mundial del coronavirus, añadiendo que fueron muy afortunados de poder terminar antes de tiempo, permitiendo que fueran capaces de pasar directamente a la fase de posproducción gracias a su equipo de editores que empezaron a trabajar desde sus casas rápidamente:

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

“¿Justo a tiempo? Fueron literalmente cinco días y el país se fue a pique. Fuimos enormemente afortunados, y entonces no pudimos esperar para empezar la posproducción. A pesar de que nos preguntábamos hasta qué punto la gente podía trabajar de manera remota, nuestro departamento de IT y ILM tenían a todo el mundo funcionando en una semana, trabajando desde casa y seguir trabajando en la sala de montaje y en las tomas de efectos visuales. Fue bastante asombroso lo rápido que se pusieron en marcha. Así que no hemos perdido tiempo.”

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Estaremos atentos a las próximas noticias para conocer más detalles de la 2ª temporada de la serie “The Mandalorian”, o incluso si se lanza un primer tráiler…

node.text:
A collage of newspaper articles from the 1918 Influenza Pandemic. It’s amazing to see the similarities to our response to Covid-19. Face masks, quarantining, closed schools, quack medicine/cures, cancelled sports, and a push for vaccines were all around 102 years ago. It’s incredible to read these articles and find so many throughlines to today. Articles date from 1918-1920 from newspapers throughout the country. Full articles can be found online at https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov.

node.text:
🇺🇸We did it!!! 
No sleep or shower for 32 hours. 🥺😬😳😱
But all packed and off we go! 
Just kidding. 
Our container left without us. 
It will also arrive way before us 😂 Ohh the joys of living in times of a pandemic...
Now off to cleaning and patching the empty house. So no worries if you don’t see any post for a little bit. I don’t even have food to cook with. 
➡️Have you ever seen a shipping container? This was my first one and I was super excited. Maybe from watching @lifeuncontained so much. ☺️Our container is already quite banged up though. Now let’s hope everything arrives safe and sound
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
🇫🇷on l’a fait !
Ni douche ni dodo pendant 32 heures. 🥺😱😬😳
Mais on a tout emballé et on est partis.
Je blague.
Le conteneur est parti sans nous.
Il arrivera aussi bien avant nous. 😂
Ohh les déménagements en période de pandémie...
Maintenant on doit tout nettoyer et réparer deux trois choses dans la maison. Alors ne vous inquiétez pas si je ne publie rien pendant quelques jours. On n’a même pas de quoi cuisiner. 
➡️Au fait, vous avez déjà vu un conteneur ? C’était mon premier et j’étais super enthousiaste. Peut-être parce qu’on regarde un peu trop @lifeuncontained ☺️ Par contre, notre conteneur est déjà pas mal abimé alors on croise les doigts pour que tout arrive bien comme il faut à destination.

Through our Power of Pads project, we are committed to ending Period Poverty in Western Kenya. Since the beginning of this global pandemic 71 million more people have been pushed into extreme poverty. This is having a detrimental impact on the lives of girls and women in the poorest communities. When money is so scarce that families can barely afford food, sanitary protection is all but forgotten. 

Even a small donation to our charity will go an extremely long way. We are setting up small businesses run by women who will make sanitary pads in their local area. Your money will go towards these projects and help us buy pads from these women to give to school girls for free. This not only provides these girls with much needed sanitary pads but gives money to the communities who are struggling more than ever during this pandemic. 

The link to our website is in our bio.

ONE WEEK! AUG 29!🎵🎶
Play Music On The Porch Day knows that music is powerful and universal. Musicians from across the globe, regardless of their differences, are finding common ground through music. Music goes beyond words. It can transcend the most difficult barriers. It ties us together like a thread through our hearts. Our skin is many colors but music is in our blood, our bones & our soul. 
🎶
At LMMO we believe in the healing power of music & want to promote this virtual event! Spread the love & share with everyone you know! 🎵
🎶
Participation is easy! Just go outside and play music. Participate alone or invite your friends to gather on the porch or your favorite place to play. 
You can register at: www.playmusicontheporchday.com 
Share a video on your social media platform & add:
#playmusicontheporchday 
🎶
PLAY IT SAFE! No large gatherings & please practice social distancing as well as all local guidelines to prevent the spread of COVID-19. 😷

What's Next,
The person I am today, Extremely Emotional yes like the emotion of vulnerability is the strength I would say the willingness to show up. Emotions are hard, but trust the pain that’s why they make you strong.I meant in a very matured way that’s healing and considering my emotions  the only priority.People who wade into discomfort and to tell the truth about their stories are the real brave hearts, recently when I was locked at home for more than 6months this pandemic I caught time to myself and made full use of it in so many ways to love myself, Art therapy, Learning new skills the most productive way also made my mind very clear about the importance of Health is wealth. We need the most love when we’re being most unlovable. And made myself really prepared for this new Change I read so much about Spirituality, Mythology and started concentrating only towards positivity spreading love. Life's too short to hold grudges. No matter how bad things get, the true test is how we choose to respond to the pain. We suffer, or inflict. It’s better to move forward than stay stuck in the past. Self-worth comes from within We can’t control what happens to us only how it affects us and the choices we must make. To the the new Life ahead to new beginning.
